<TITLE> Knit Exposition 2007 begins Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 1 (bdnews24.com)  The Knit Exposition 2007, a knitwear show, begins Sunday at the Hotel Sheraton in the capital. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed is expected to inaugurate the exposition at 11am, president of Bangladesh Knitwear Manufacturers and Exporters Association, Fazlul Hoque, said at a press conference. Hoque said, "The sign of recession in knitwear export that we saw early in the year has disappeared. We hope the earnings from exports in the sector will exceed the target by end of the year." He said buyers from the US, Canada, France, Spain, Italy, Germany, the UK, India, Pakistan and Nepal will visit the exposition boasting 51 stalls. Entry to the fair was restricted, Hoque said, adding that only those involved with garments industry were eligible of visit the exposition. bdnew
